heaviest_rainrate.status: There was a torrential downpour today where the rain reached a maximum intensity of 16.2mm per hour (ranked 4th in our records).  The storm lasted 6.9 hours and 9.36mm of precipitation fell during that time.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 2.2°C), outside temperature (down 2.0°C), and inside temperature (down 1.7°C), more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%), and drier conditions in rainfall (down 0.1 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 643 m), rainfall (up 0.1 mm), and light levels (up 5958 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1241 m), light levels (up 7880 lux), and rainfall (down 0.4 mm) when compared to today.
